						<p>We know that the fastest moving entity is light. However, quantum entanglement suggests that tiny particles interact with each other at a rate faster than the speed of light, such that they are cannot be described independently of each other. Albert Einstein thought this very strange and referred to it as “spooky action at a distance.</p>
						<a href="Blogpost.html" class="btn btn-primary">Read more >></a>
					</div></a>
				</div>
			</div>

			<!-- Latest blog posts -->
			<div class="row section">
				<div class="col-md-12">
					<h3>Latest stories</h3>
				</div>
			</div>

			<!-- Blog Post Query goes here. -->
		
        @{
        	var selection = Umbraco.Content(Guid.Parse("39e702cf-f850-423b-8c3b-47e052f26cf3"))
            .ChildrenOfType("blogItem")
            .Where(x => x.IsVisible())
            .OrderByDescending(x => x.CreateDate);
        }
        <div class="row">
        	@foreach (var item in selection)
        	{
        			var thumbnail = item.Value<IPublishedContent>("thumbnailImage");
        			<div class="col-md-4">
						<a href="@item.Url()" class="featured-link"><div class="thumbnail-blog">
